    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Breed of horse characterized by being tall, slim, most notably used for racing and jumping. It was developed in England; the origin may be traced back to records indicating that a stock of Arab and Barb horses was introduced into England as early as the 3rd century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
